Package: revdeplite
Type: Package
Title: Lightweight Reverse Dependency Checks
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Brantly", family = "Callaway", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "brantly.callaway@uga.edu")
    )
Description: A lightweight alternative to the 'revdepcheck' package for running
    reverse dependency checks. Uses packages already installed in the local
    library rather than building isolated libraries from scratch, which can be
    dramatically faster when most dependencies are already present. Installs the
    local package, upgrades only what is missing or outdated, and runs R CMD
    check on each reverse dependency. Also supports checking GitHub development
    versions of packages alongside CRAN releases.
SystemRequirements: git (for github_deps support in simple_revdep_check())
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: rcmdcheck, utils, tools
Suggests: pak, devtools, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
